Term Project: Kaggle Classification and Write-Up

---

OVERVIEW

This term project is an open-ended applied NLP task with two main objectives:

1. Apply course concepts to a real-world classification problem
2. Practice technical communication by clearly explaining your approach

---

WHO MUST COMPLETE THIS

Required:
Graduate-level students (LING 539, CSC 539, INFO 539)

Optional / Exempt:
Undergraduate-level students (LING 439, CSC 439, ISTA 439)

---

THE TASK

You will:

* Build a classification system using a dataset from a private Kaggle competition
* Use at least one algorithm covered in class
* Submit predictions to Kaggle and track performance on the leaderboard
* Iteratively improve your model (multiple submissions allowed)

